==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drumstick
<hw>Drum"stick`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
stick with which a drum is beaten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything resembling a drumstick in form; -- applied
especially to the tibiotarsus, or second joint, of the leg of a fowl,
when cooked and served at the table.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drum winding</ent>⟦br⟧
